{
  "doc_id": "45883",
  "text": "Suppose now that there is an error in the centriole duplication where the mother centriole has two or more daughter centrioles. Suppose further that this defect of overduplication persists so that there are numerous centrioles, or \"supernumerary\" centrioles within the cell. Suppose still further that due to electromagnetic field interactions these multiple centrioles cluster together as is characteristic of cancer cells [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Then the resulting electromagnetic field of the cluster is presumed to be many times greater than that of a single centriole pair. For some cancerous tumors, specifically breast cancers, this increase in electromagnetism can even be measured at the breast surface [CITATION_3] [62].",
